About Daniel: As the first in his family to go to college, Daniel attended the University of Arizona where he interned for then-Congresswoman Gabby Giffords. Daniel was a survivor of the 2011 Tucson shooting and was the first to administer first aid before EMTs arrived on the scene. Turning tragedy into resilience, Daniel decided to live a life of public service to protect Arizonan families and served on the Sunnyside School board (2011-2015) and was later elected to the Arizona State Legislature (2017-2022). Now, Daniel is running for Congress to Fight the Trump Administration to protect Arizonans' social security and healthcare access, expand federal dollars into public education, and lower the cost of everyday goods and housing.

title: 15th Congressional District Town Hall
description:
The 15th District has been targeted by the Democratic Congressional Campaign Committee as one that is vulnerable. We can affect the makeup of Congress by making our voices heard.

Our representative Mike Carey has REFUSED to face his constituents. We've called, we've visited his office, we've emailed, and we have sent him a certified invitation. 

No response!

People are upset. And they should be - but we are getting louder and refuse to back down. Our elected representative should WANT to listen to our concerns. It's his job.

We are holding a town hall to hear from YOU. We will meet to express our opinions about the votes Mike Carey has taken to cut Social Security, jobs, healthcare, cutting taxes for the very wealthy, and destroying ciimate initiatives. 

We've invited previous candidates from the 15th District to share their experiences running for Congress, and ways we can make a difference in our District. Sign up now to hear how we can work together to speak to our Congressional representative.

title: 15th Congressional District Town Hall
description:

Our representative Mike Carey has REFUSED to face his constituents. We've called, we've visited his office, we've emailed, and we have sent him a certified invitation.

No response!

People are upset. And they should be - but we are getting louder and refuse to back down. Our elected representative should WANT to listen to our concerns. It's his job.

We are holding a town hall to hear from YOU. We will meet to express our opinions about the votes Mike Carey has taken to cut Social Security, jobs, healthcare, cutting taxes for the very wealthy, and destroying climate initiatives.

We've invited previous candidates from the 15th District to share their experiences running for Congress, and ways we can make a difference in our District. Sign up now to hear how we can work together to speak to our Congressional representative.

title: May 31- Stand Up for Democracy - Seminole County Protest

location.venue: Parking lots along 17-92 near Casselberry City Hall

description:
Trump has gone too far. He is abusing authority and undermining the foundations of our democracy.

Stand up for democracy with us! Join our peaceful demonstration on Saturday, May 31, from 10 am to noon along South 17-92 in Casselberry.

We will gather along South Highway 17-92 between East Melody Lane and Triplet Lake Dr. (This is near the Casselberry Target but on the OTHER SIDE of the street.) There is parking close to the sidewalks. 

Our focus is on being visible to passing cars and showing that we love America. We encourage people to wear red, white and blue, and bring flags to wave. 

If you aren't able to stand by the road with us, then drive by and honk! 

Bring your favorite sign with a message that is meaningful to you. Or you can borrow one of our signs to hold while you are there. 

To make a sign, buy foam board at Dollar Tree or other discount stores. Be sure to decorate both sides. Thick markers work well.

You can also sign up for a SemDems sign-making event, or come to the SemDems office during office hours to use supplies to make a sign there.

**Please note** A core principle behind our actions is a commitment to nonviolence in all we do. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with our values.

This event will also be posted on the fiftyfifty.one website.
